-- Chrysler says second-quarter vehicle shipments to rise at least 13 percent
-- 
-- Mon Apr 29, 2013 10:35am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/04/29/us-chrysler-shipments-idUSBRE93S0FE20130429

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Chrysler Group LLC says that it will increase its vehicle shipments in the second quarter by at least 13 percent from the previous quarter. 
 Shipments from April through June will be at least 650,000, up from 574,000 in the first quarter, Chrysler said in a slide presentation after it issued quarterly earnings on Monday. Of the vehicles the company shipped in the first quarter, 73 percent went to the U.S. market, up from 69 percent a year earlier. (Reporting by  Bernie Woodall ; Editing by Gerald E. McCormick)